### Use getTransaction to get current transaction reference

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/Migration Guide.md

The `newrelic.getTransaction()` method retrieves a reference to the currently executing transaction. It is essential for advanced transaction management, especially when used with `startWebTransaction`, `startBackgroundTransaction`, or callback-based message consumers to ensure proper transaction lifecycle management.

```javascript
/**
 * New method: newrelic.getTransaction()
 */
newrelic.startWebTransaction('MyTransaction', function() {
  const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();

  // You can now use the transaction object for further operations,
  // for example, recording exceptions or ending the transaction explicitly.
  try {
    // ... perform work ...
    if (someCondition) {
      transaction.recordExcepion(new Error('Something went wrong'));
    }
    transaction.end();
  } catch (error) {
    transaction.recordExcepion(error);
    transaction.end();
    throw error;
  }
});

```

