### Start Transactions Manually in New Relic Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

These methods allow for manual initiation of New Relic transactions, providing more control over transaction naming and management. `newrelic.startWebTransaction` is used for web requests, while `newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction` is for background processes. Documentation also covers the `TransactionHandle` class returned by `getTransaction`.

```javascript
newrelic.startWebTransaction('Custom/Web/Transaction', () => {
  // Transaction logic here
});

newrelic.startBackgroundTransaction('Custom/Background/Job', () => {
  // Transaction logic here
});

const transaction = newrelic.getTransaction();
// Use transaction handle for further operations
```

