### Add Custom Parameters to Transactions (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet demonstrates how to use the `addCustomParameters()` API method in the New Relic Node.js agent to add multiple custom parameters to a transaction at once. This is useful for enriching transaction data with specific application context. It requires the New Relic agent to be initialized.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// ... inside a transaction context ...
newrelic.addCustomParameters({
  "key1": "value1",
  "key2": "value2"
});
```

