### Node.js: New Relic API for Transaction Naming

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet illustrates the use of the New Relic module's exported API for naming transactions and defining URL to transaction name mapping rules. This API is crucial for customizing how requests are displayed and aggregated in the New Relic UI, especially when not using frameworks like Express or Restify.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// Example: Naming a transaction
newrelic.setTransactionName('Custom/User/Login');

// Example: Adding a URL to transaction name mapping rule
newrelic.addCustomRule('transaction_name', { // This is a placeholder, actual API usage may differ
  request_uri: '/api/v1/users/*',
  transaction_name: 'Custom/API/Users'
});
```

