### Associating User IDs with Transactions - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

With v9.13.0, the `setUserID` API method was added to associate a unique identifier with transaction events, traces, and errors. This identifier, stored as `enduser.id`, facilitates tracking specific user activity and debugging issues related to individual users.

```javascript
newrelic.setUserID('user-123');
```
